<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="743" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/23494.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Mediators</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Answering the note
                            submitted by you and your colleagues, Ministers Naón and Suárez, I beg
                            to say that notice of General Huerta’s acceptance of mediation is
                            received with satisfaction. We note what you say in regard to suspension
                            of hostilities during mediation. We so understand it, provided of course
                            that this Governnient would be at liberty to repel any aggression
                            attempted.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>